<br>
Why?!<br>
<br>
Somebody refute my assertion that the people who designed and developed the most successful MMORPG to date are capable of:<br>
<br>
1. Kunark mobs have a maximum of 32,000 hitpoints<br>
2. 32000 hitpoits / 4 wizards = 8000 damage per wizard.<br>
3. 8000 damage / 2 dmg-mana ratio on MB = 4000 mana required<br>
4. Yes, there are plenty of wizards with 4000 mana or better.<br>
<br>
I'm a software developer myself.  There's no possible way a group of designers/developers capable of implementing a game as complex as EQ are not also capable of making these assertions.  You're a fool if you think SOE is going to &quot;discover&quot; this possibility from the players.  I can 100% guarantee that when this ability was conceived, somebody over there went through this.<br>
<br>
Once again: if they nerf it, it won't be becuase it wasn't kept secret.  It will be because the ability is entering the game faster than they intended, or that there is some item dropping off a low HP mob that now enters the game faster than they intended.<br>
<br>
