Good point.  Still, this isn't some obscure phenomenon.  This is basic design:<br>
<br>
Designer_01: &quot;Hey, I think an ability that used all mana in one giant unresistable nuke would be cool for wizards.&quot;<br>
Developer_02: &quot;That would be doable, and cool.  What would make sense for the mana-damage ratio?&quot;<br>
<br>
[Insert the exact crunching of numbers I've already described... if you could even call that number crunching.]<br>
<br>
Design_Team_Manager_01: &quot;Ok, a variable rate between 1.5 and 2.0 will work.  Naturally some mobs are going to get easier, some even trivial, but you can't allow players to get more powerful AND keep the same level of difficulty for existing encounters.&quot;<br>
